// Description:
//	This code is the brain of the self-installing package. Thank this code, the bin-package allows you to install or remove
//	the target software using the following CLI:
//		<pkg bin-file> {--install|--uninstall} [--verbose] [--hwelp]
//
//	Internal structure of bin package
//		+-----------------+
//		| Python launcher | The packqage's brain
//		+-----------------+
//		|                 |
//		| tar.gz payload  | TGZ archive that contains the files to install
//		|                 |
//		+-----------------+
//		| Footer          |
//		+-----------------+
//
//	In order to manage the TGZ collected data, I have used the UNIX common archive library. In the following table you can
//	read the exit code of the functions belong to the library
//
//		ARCHIVE_OK      = successo
//		ARCHIVE_WARN    = successo con warning
//		ARCHIVE_RETRY   = riprova l'operazione
//		ARCHIVE_FAILED  = operazione fallita, ma l'archivio può continuare
//		ARCHIVE_FATAL   = errore irreversibile, fermati
//		ARCHIVE_EOF     = fine archivio (solo per alcune API)
//
//
//	Exit code convention:
//		0..15      Success / informational
//		16..127    Non-fatal conditions (warnings)
//		128..255   Fatal errors (logMsg() terminates the program)
//
//
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
